 the point where the unit-context model's 
\size small

\begin_inset Formula $S_{y_{a}}^{2*}/S_{y_{a}}^{2}$
\end_inset


\size default
 is closer to 1 in that area.
 Hence, estimates are biased for some areas more than for others.
\end_layout

